			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The making of a Jedi within the framework of an online game. How would a player 'have the force'...
<br />

<br />
I believe that a player should search for a Jedi master (the first quest), then successfully perform the quests assigned by the master. After the completion of each quest, his Force strength would increase culminating in the final quest that would grant him/her the title of Master. This would allow the player to have the sense of achievement. And if the quests are properly done, the level of difficulty rising with each quest, the difficulty would increase, making the powerful Jedi a rare commodity. This approch does NOT limit the number of Jedis per se, but does limit the number of Jedis that have the strength and power of Yoda.
<br />

<br />
After all, in real life... How many people out there have the technical right to wear a Karate Black Belt but in truth have only 'purchased' the belt rather than concientiously practiced the art?
<br />

<br />
Just my two cents...</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
