			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am glad to see that you are turning to the community for thier input on Jedi. I'd hate to log into a server and find everyone Master Jedi. So here are my thoughts on becoming a Jedi.
<br />

<br />
1. Force sensitiviy should be random and the player shouold not be made aware of this right away. Perhaps other more powerful Jedi could "sense" they have the gift and offer to train them in the ways of the force. 
<br />

<br />
2. To become a TRUE Jedi should require dedication and training. Now I say a true Jedi meaning a Master Jedi. The casual gamer could still be Jedi with the use of force powers but to allow someone to become a Master in a short time would result in Jedi overkill in the world. The Master Jedi would be the most powerful out of all the Jedi. To reach such a status should require a HUGE time commitment to thier character. True, the casual gamer will complain--alot that he or she can never obtain the status of MAster Jedi. That would be untrue. To reach the status would seem to take longer because they only play a few hours a week. But in that few hours, thier training should show some progress.
<br />

<br />
3. To keep the number of Jedi down, I think the intensive traing and dedication should aid in achieving this goal. That's not to say there will be numerous players with some force abilites after a little training, there should should be some folks like that. The only difference between them and a Jedi...the Jedi can harness the power to its full effectiveness. 
<br />

<br />
4. The balancing issue is a tough one. On one hand if you do not balance them, every non-jedi will be complaining and wanting thier proffesions upgraded to be in line with the Jedi power. On the other hand, if a player spend the time to train, they should be rewarded with better abilities and powers that allows them to outperform the other professions. I'm with the later. Let's face it do you really think a merchant or bounty hunter or smuggler could go toe to toe with a jedi,whether they are fully trained or not? No. A highly skilled stormtrooper taking well aimed shots a jedi charging at them, shouldn't stand a chance. At the same time, a team of highly skilled stormtroopers working together and employing strategic millitary tactics should stand a chance against the jedi(not a Master however)and may be able to take the jedi out.
<br />
    So, no do not balance the trained jedi against the other professions as this will upset the idea behind the force and those who train to harness the power of the force.
<br />

<br />
4. Acting like a jedi...hmmm. The two roles of jedi(dark and light) makes it hard to "act accordingly". Light Jedi who do not uphold to thier values and perform evil acts turn into Dark Jedi. And let's face it, Dark Jedi pretty much do what they want. They are evil and acting evil means breaking the rules that scociety has set forth. In your FAQ, you mentioned that playing Dark Jedi would be perilous. I take that to mean--a very rough life. At the same time, it also means that a player is able to function in the role of Dark Jedi within the gaming world but they just need to watch thier backs. So, with this in mind to make sure that Light Jedi "act accordingly" make evil acts(I'll let you fill the meaning within the game's system  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" border="0" /> )performed by Light Jedi lead to the path of the Dark Side. As far as Dark Jedi acting properly, if they are not acting dark lead them to the path of the light (jk). The Dark Jedi should be hunted by Light Jedi and maybe even bounty hunters every waking moment of a Dark Jedi's life. 
<br />

<br />
To summarize, force sensitve should be randomize. This will not stop someone from creating a character over and over until they get a force sensitive character but the dedication and training that would be required, along with the Trials to be considered a Jedi should cut down on the number of Jedi running around. Jedis should be powerful but vulnerable--if non-jedi were to go head on with a Jedi they wouldn't stand a chance. Acting like a jedi would be dependant upon which side of the force they serve. Light acting evil should turn Dark and as a Dark your life should be in jepoardy every waking moment.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
