				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">What a great topic. 
<br />

<br />
1) Force sensitivity should not be random. Players should be able to toggle it upon creation. BUT and this is a BIG but... its gotta come at a price. Remember Lord Vader took a great deal of time to hunt down and kill most of the Jedi. The emperor didn't give him a super star destroyer and a vast army just to go tooling around in. You can bet he spent a good part of the time finding force sensitive individuals and either... 
<br />
Recruited them to work for the Empire under close supervision (possibly looking for other force sensitive individuals).. or.. had them terminated. You could write it so that the more time a player speands near a Imperial facility or garrison, the greater chance they may be "picked up" by a force monitor. They would be given the offer to join or die.. you get the idea past here..Bounty hunters, Imperial forces (AI)targeting this individual more often than other individual.. etc.. 
<br />

<br />
You could also have PC's working for the empire hunting down other PC's with force sensitivity. Add an element of paranoia to this. 
<br />

<br />
This way you get to still try to make Jedi status with a HUGE penalty. Your scared for your life most of the time, and other players are hunting you down.
<br />

<br />
2) Players become Jedi by finding a master, and completing "Trials". Masters would be far away, hidden and secluded. They don't want to attract Imperial attention either. There would only be a certain number of "Masters" and each "master" would only be able to take on one pupil at a time. Thats in the Jedi code. You guys could easily control the number of masters to your own liking. If you find you have too many "masters" just make sure the Empire finds em.. an dthey can be removed. If to few.. you can have some emerge from hiding.
<br />

<br />
3) The mysterious factor.. well, being able to do things normal people can't does that automaticaly. They are going off to very difficult and secluded area's for prolonged periods of time.. IE.. Luke went away for a few months and came back fully able to take care of Jabba's minions and Boba-fett with little assistance. Jedi Trials/training should be secluded and the trials themselves should teach the jedi his role in the universe. 
<br />

<br />
4) balancing Jedi.. What do you mean.. balancing Jedi.. The mere thought of going against the jedi made several members of the Trade federation question their superiors mental states... they are feared for a reason, they put up with HUGE obsticles to advance and they have to find a master.. limiting thier numbers greatly. They SHOULD be FAR more powerful than any player could be. I think players would realise this if the bar was set THAT high the players involved DESERVED to be there. 
<br />

<br />
5) Incentives? Yeah, thats a tough one. Thats the TOUGHEST one. I'll get back to you on that. I need time to think</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
