			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First, The force sensitive ability should be choosen at character creation, but at a serious sacrifice in other ability areas.  Not just a minor annoyance, the choice to possibly become a jedi should be a serious decision.  If you noticed i stated possibly become a jedi, because becoming a jedi should be an organic process of teacher and student.  The best way to limit jedi is start out with a few jedi masters (perhaps 4), and each one can take on only one padawan at a time.  The jedi master can then teach the student his/her powers as they complete quests for the master.  Depending on how this is implemented it may take a player 2 or 3 months before they become a jedi capable of teaching other students.  Of course, over time more and more jedi will appear, but is will limit the amount because a force sensitive character must seek out a player jedi to teach them.  So a character may be force sensitive but never find a master to teach them, or have to wait until the master no longer has a padawan.  The first 4 jedi should be highly trusted players or employees of VI.  They can then monitor the behavior ot the padawan they have choosen, if a padawan does not act jedi enough then they can refuse to teach them further.  If they pass the "tests" then you know you will have high caliber jedi who can be trusted to train other jedi.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
