			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">1.) "How would a player get to be Force Sensitive?"  
<br />
     I think that everyone should be "born" with some measure of the force. The true amount would only be able to be measured at a "Jedi Center" through a blood test for the Midichloriens (unsure of spelling)that would give the character an idea of what their base force potential is. 
<br />
2.) "How would a player get to be a Jedi?"
<br />

<br />
     Then, if he should choose the life of a Jedi, he could enroll in  an academy where he would receive intermediate force training (quests and missions designed to focus on defensive abilities and responsibilities not dependant upon levels, but on the completion of assignments)up to the rank, if he chooses, of Padowan. (If he chooses not to, he could still retain some of the ablilities acquired.) I would set up Padowan to have about 10 levels or degrees of training; each level would consist of suitable missions and quests still focusing mainly on the defensive and healing powers of the force. At the end of the 10th degree, he would graduate to Padowan Apprentice (10 levels/degrees) and begin his first training in the offensive powers and skills of the force in which he would receive his first lightsaber also. His next 10 levels would be enjoyed as a Sr. Apprentice completing quests and missions as he progressed. Then, he could take the trials (very specially designed missions)to attain the level of Jedi Master. The master would still continue to grow in his force ability also.
<br />

<br />
3.) "How do you make Jedi feel rare and mysterious?"
<br />
     The young padowan would not be able to use any force abilities outside of academy assignments until his first level of apprenticeship. And, a jedi at any level using force powers in view of Emperial forces, would recieve a "Faction Warrant" after a certain number had been accumulated, the Empire would send a bounty hunter or team of bounty hunters; depending on level; to eliminate them. That would create the paranoia that Jedi should feel in such a time of war.
<br />

<br />
4.) "Would you try to balance the Jedi profession against others? If so, how?"
<br />

<br />
     Making the Jedi's power something he cannot openly flaunt without recourse, would create a type of balance in itself. Most of the time, he would have to fight as a regular player. Possibly make Jedi like a second profession and their main skills would follow that profession as far as how they perform and appear...only when using their significant Jedi powers, would they be identifiable as a Jedi. (Limits similar to a caster not being able to cast spells when wearing certain types of armor in certain rpgs would be imposed also).
<br />

<br />
5.) "What incentives to you give to have Jedi players “act appropriately”?"
<br />

<br />
     I propose a system similar to the "Faction Warrant" mentioned above that would take place when a Jedi did something against character. When enough warrants had built up, the Jedi Council would issue a probation warrant. The subject would be summoned using bounty hunters to the nearest Jedi facility for punishment (if they wish to keep being a light Jedi, they could perform special tasks as pennance). If the the character wished to become a dark Jedi, then at that time, he would strike down those sent for him and thereby initiate himself into the darkside.
<br />
   Sorry for so much clamor, but i'm REALLY looking forward to this game.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
